item.title: sayDIE add a quote by F. Scott Fitzgerald
item.description: "Their point of resemblance to each other and their difference from so many American women, lay in the fact that they were all happy to exist in a man's world--they preserved their individuality through men and not by opposition to them. They would all three have made alternatively good courtesans or good wives not by the accident of birth but through the greater accident of finding their man or not finding him." -- F. Scott Fitzgerald
